{"type":"message","id":"eb71696e","parentId":"3d244010","timestamp":"2026-03-29T22:09:53.601Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to continue conversation. The user asked /start again. We have already done the intro. We should ask what they want to work on. Let's respond with a friendly message, following double line breaks.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"• Hey Ivek! Great to see you again. 👋\n\n• Our workspace is all set up with Notion integration ready to go.\n\n• I'm bbymama, your friendly AI assistant here to help with coding, brainstorming, organizing, or whatever you need.\n\n• What would you like to work on today?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":21846,"output":114,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21960,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774822186665,"responseId":"chatcmpl-9e85a137360546e6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"cb4fa8a2","parentId":"eb71696e","timestamp":"2026-03-29T22:11:09.400Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"635\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"6735239700\",\n  \"sender\": \"Ivek\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-30 00:11 GMT+2\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Ivek (6735239700)\",\n  \"id\": \"6735239700\",\n  \"name\": \"Ivek\"\n}\n```\n\ncan you summarize the 3 key point of 3 top videos on youtube for \"openclaw\". use youtube-research skill"}],"timestamp":1774822269396}}
{"type":"message","id":"0d2c205b","parentId":"cb4fa8a2","timestamp":"2026-03-29T22:11:12.258Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to use youtube-research skill. First read its SKILL.md to know how. Then run tool? Probably we need to call youtube-research? Actually skill provides instructions. We'll need to use web_search? There's a youtube-research skill file. Let's read it.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_274d3f665e40490b9165e6c4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/skills/youtube-research/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":22085,"output":103,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22188,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774822269400,"responseId":"chatcmpl-9bc081f9e7aa39f3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"92457a4b","parentId":"0d2c205b","timestamp":"2026-03-29T22:11:12.275Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_274d3f665e40490b9165e6c4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: youtube-research\ndescription: Search YouTube videos, extract transcripts, and analyze content using YouTube Data API v3. Use when the user asks to (1) search for YouTube videos on any topic, (2) get recent/popular videos about a subject, (3) transcribe or extract captions from videos, (4) get technical details (duration, views, resolution, etc.), (5) summarize video content, or (6) compare multiple videos. Works with video URLs or search queries.\n---\n\n# YouTube Research\n\nSearch, transcribe, and analyze YouTube content.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```bash\n# Search for videos\npython scripts/youtube_search.py --search \"python async\" --max 5\n\n# Get video details\npython scripts/youtube_search.py --video VIDEO_ID --details\n\n# Get transcript\npython scripts/youtube_search.py --video VIDEO_ID --transcript\n\n# Full analysis (details + transcript)\npython scripts/youtube_search.py --video VIDEO_ID --full\n```\n\n## Requirements\n\n- `YOUTUBE_KEY` in `.env` file (YouTube Data API v3 key)\n- Python 3.6+ (standard library only for basic usage)\n- `yt-dlp` for reliable transcript extraction: install via pip, apt, or download binary\n\n**Install yt-dlp:**\n```bash\n# Option 1: pip (recommended)\npip install yt-dlp\n\n# Option 2: apt (Linux)\nsudo apt install yt-dlp\n\n# Option 3: Download binary (any OS)\n# See: https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp#installation\n```\n\n**Note:** Search and video details work without yt-dlp. Transcript extraction requires yt-dlp.\n\n## Core Workflows\n\n### 1. Search Videos\n\n```bash\n# By relevance (default)\npython scripts/youtube_search.py --search \"machine learning\" --max 10\n\n# Most recent first\npython scripts/youtube_search.py --search \"machine learning\" --order date\n\n# Most viewed\npython scripts/youtube_search.py --search \"machine learning\" --order viewCount\n```\n\nOutput includes: title, URL, channel, publish date, description preview.\n\n### 2. Get Video Details\n\n```bash\npython scripts/youtube_search.py --video VIDEO_ID --details\n```\n\nReturns: title, description, duration, view count, likes, comments, resolution, caption availability, tags.\n\n### 3. Get Transcript\n\n```bash\npython scripts/youtube_search.py --video VIDEO_ID --transcript\npython scripts/youtube_search.py --video VIDEO_ID --transcript --lang es  # Spanish\n```\n\nReturns: full transcript text, timestamped segments, word count.\n\n### 4. Summarize Content\n\nAfter getting transcript, use the AI to summarize:\n\n```\nUser: \"Summarize the key points from this transcript\"\nUser: \"What are the 5 main takeaways?\"\nUser: \"Explain the section starting at 5:30\"\n```\n\n## Common Patterns\n\n### \"What are the recent videos on X?\"\n\n1. Search with `--order date`\n2. Present top 5 results briefly\n3. Ask if user wants details/transcript on any\n\n### \"Summarize this video: URL\"\n\n1. Extract video ID from URL\n2. Get details (for context)\n3. Get transcript\n4. Summarize key points\n5. Offer to expand on sections\n\n### \"Compare the top 3 videos about X\"\n\n1. Search with `--max 3`\n2. Get details for each\n3. Get transcripts for each\n4. Provide comparative analysis\n\n### \"What does this video say about Y?\"\n\n1. Get transcript\n2. Search transcript for relevant keywords\n3. Quote relevant sections with timestamps\n\n## Video ID Extraction\n\nThe script handles these formats:\n- `https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID`\n- `https://youtu.be/VIDEO_ID`\n- Direct `VIDEO_ID`\n\n## Output Formats\n\n```bash\n# Human-readable (default)\npython scripts/youtube_search.py --search \"topic\" --max 5\n\n# JSON for processing\npython scripts/youtube_search.py --search \"topic\" --json\n\n# Brief (one line per video)\npython scripts/youtube_search.py --search \"topic\" --brief\n```\n\n## Limitations\n\n- Transcript extraction depends on YouTube's caption availability\n- Auto-generated captions may have errors\n- Some videos have no captions available\n\n### Fallback: yt-dlp\n\nWhen transcript extraction fails:\n\n```bash\nyt-dlp --write-auto-sub --sub-lang en --skip-download \"URL\"\n```\n\n## Advanced Usage\n\nSee [references/advanced.md](references/advanced.md) for:\n- Search query optimization\n- Timestamp-based navigation\n- Summarization patterns\n- Rate limits and error handling\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774822272272}}
