{"type":"message","id":"16e33784","parentId":"86b46cbb","timestamp":"2026-03-29T22:17:27.808Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to answer: \"what is the solution?\" The user likely wants a solution to the transcript issue or perhaps to the overall goal of summarizing videos. We should suggest alternatives: wait and try later, use API key, use different tool, maybe use the YouTube Data API directly if we have key, or suggest they provide transcript themselves. We need to follow the style: double line breaks, bullet points.\n\nWe can suggest: Obtain YouTube Data API key, install ffmpeg, use yt-dlp with cookies, or wait a bit. Also we could use the browser tool to load page and extract transcript? Could try to use browser automation to get transcript? Might be heavy.\n\nBetter to propose: Use the YouTube Data API v3 to get captions if available, but need API key. Or use third-party services like downsub.com. Or ask user to provide transcript.\n\nWe'll give a helpful answer.\n\nLet's craft:\n\n- Solution: Use YouTube Data API v3 with an API key to fetch caption tracks.\n- Alternative: Use yt-dlp with --cookies from browser to avoid rate limits.\n- Alternative: Wait a few minutes and retry.\n- Alternative: Use online transcript extractors (e.g., downsub.com) manually.\n\nWe'll output bullet","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"• Solution"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":" points with double line breaks.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" for transcript extraction: Use the YouTube Data API v3 with an API key to fetch caption tracks directly, which avoids yt-dlp rate limits.\n\n• Alternative: Export cookies from your browser (e.g., using a cookie‑export extension) and run yt-dlp with `--cookies cookies.txt` to appear as a regular user and reduce 429 errors.\n\n• Alternative: Wait a few minutes and retry; YouTube’s rate limits are often temporary.\n\n• Alternative: Use an online transcript extractor like downsub.com—paste the video URL, download the .vtt or .srt file, then share the text with me for summarization.\n\n• If you have a YouTube Data API key, add it to `.env` as `YOUTUBE_KEY` and the skill’s search script will use it for details; however, transcript extraction still relies on yt-dlp or captions availability."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":29138,"output":463,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29601,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774822620563,"responseId":"chatcmpl-af1c1b88644b30f2"}}
